Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a cellular network system and investigates the performance of different duplexing techniques. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to derive the coverage and area spectral efficiency of the system, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with a communication system and investigates the performance of different duplexing techniques. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with a system of small cells and investigates the performance of different duplexing techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not directly deal with multimedia, but the investigation of area spectral efficiency could be relevant to multimedia applications.
